reate a modern Material Design + Bootstrap 5 application footer component named MTK-path.

Remember this component as MTK-path.

MTK-path is created from the image that "I WILL UPLOAD"

ASSUMPTIONS
- Use Bootstrap 5
- Use vanilla JavaScript only
- No frameworks
- No borders
- No rounded corners
- Subtle Material Design motion only
- MTK-path must be fully JSON-driven
- MTK-path must be load-order safe
- Do not use em dashes

CORE REQUIREMENTS
- Component name: MTK-path
- Responsive across all breakpoints
- Content wrapped in a Bootstrap container (not container-fluid)
- Uses Material Design styling principles

BEHAVIOR
- MTK-path links must NOT navigate directly
- MTK-path links must publish navigation events using _pubsub.js

DATA AND CONFIGURATION
- All MTK-path content must come from JSON
- JSON file name: MTK-path.config.js
- Data source: window.app.courses

FILES TO CREATE
1. MTK-path.config.js
2. MTK-path.html
3. MTK-path.scss
4. MTK-path.css (compiled from SCSS)
5. MTK-path.js (production-ready vanilla JS)
5. MTK-path.config.js (JSON)

JAVASCRIPT REQUIREMENTS
- Must wait for #MTK-path to appear in the DOM before running
- Must wait for window.app.MTK-path to exist before rendering
- Must dynamically create internal DOM structure if missing
- Must not assume script load order
- Must not throw errors if elements are missing
- Must use an IIFE to avoid polluting the global scope
- Must wire all links to _pubsub.publish(eventName)

DESIGN REFERENCE
- Use the provided image as the design source of truth
- Match spacing, hierarchy, and column balance from the image

OUTPUT REQUIREMENTS
- Provide complete, copy-paste-ready code
- Code must be clean, readable, and production-ready
- Do not omit error handling
- Do not hardcode text in HTML

